Meanwhile, undisclosed sponsorship can't even be proven because it's supposed to be undisclosed. No one can tell if no one hears about it.

I'd rather stick to tinfoil antenna's whispers that it's a sponsorship deal to artificially extend the game's relevancy by making them stream one by one even if they don't like fps games, rather than cover being silly inefficient by getting individual permission for every member one by one instead of as a collective whole.

Or just mix the two theory and it's not a sponsorship but permissions are being given one by anyway for the same reason. And all holomems have a sudden urge to play competitive fps games for some reason.
author: @fatcat1250

text:
¬†@fatcat1250¬† "Short streams"
Ame's stream - 3+ hours
Mumei's stream - 3+ hours (SC reading portion deducted)
IRyS streams - 5+ hours for both streams (SC reading portion deducted)

Maybe they just saw each other playing it and decided to try it out, which is what happened to literally every new games released (Splatoon 3, Overwatch 2, etc) or games they just got perms for (Factorio), not everything has to be a conspiracy theory. Also, not sure why you even bring up "individual permission", that's not even what Miles meant, he was just referring to each person jumping into the same game right after Cover got them the perms.
